- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the problem of bandwidth aggregation in multi-homed devices, which is a networking issue. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as the paper may discuss security concerns related to bandwidth aggregation. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as bandwidth aggregation can be used to improve performance in distributed systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper may discuss control mechanisms for bandwidth aggregation. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper may discuss theoretical aspects of bandwidth aggregation.
